8:
Nothing's ever "good" when it comes
to you. Especially not when you
want something. Goodbye.
14:
Oh, don't be like that. I just want to
show off my latest piece of loot.
17:
Snagged it during a job. Apparently
it lets you hear the voices of the
dead!
21:
...Are you serious? That sounds super
sketchy...
24:
Why would I lie? With this, I can get
tons of info that no one else knows
about!
27:
I guess you're not wrong to be wary,
though. Say, you know a couple
experts on this kinda stuff, right? You
should introduce—
37:
Rgh... Aha, what is this... I feel like I'm
gonna die... Help—
47:
You're plagued by the thoughts and
emotions of the dead. In other
words, you're afflicted by a curse.
49:
...Forcefully removing it might cost
you your life.
57:
Where did you procure such an
object?
66:
I dunno about this guy, Alk. The
voices... They're pretty scared of
him... Argh!
70:
My everything hurts! I feel sick to my
stomach too! No way I can
remember where I got it in this state!
74:
You know it's to your benefit to be
honest right now, yeah?!
78: Alk. Do you consider him your ally?
83:
Though he may be questionable
most of the time, we do share a
bond of sorts.
87:
Yeah. As much as I think this is
karma at work, I do feel a little bad.
93:
Oh, come on, do you gotta be so
mean? I thought we were friends!
97:
Adjudicus, have mercy on me,
please! I know they're acting like
they don't care, but they'd be happy
to see you save my skin!
101:
Is that all you have to say for
yourself?
105:
I'm afraid a simple run-of-the-mill
guy like me can only beg for help!
110:
So he says, but he's actually a pretty
skilled informant. I'm sure you could
find a use for him.
115:
H-hey, what'd you go and tell him
that for?! I don't wanna do business
with a guy that reeks of death!
118:
I'm not sure this is how you should
be addressing the dude that could
potentially save your life...
123:
...Heh. I don't mind. If this is who you
wish saved, then so be it.
126:
I can prepare a suit of armor that
will suppress the effects of the
curse. As for everything after that...
it's up to you.
132:
...And that's how I ended up like this.
Ain't that something?
135:
Goodness. Well, you seem to have a
grasp of things at least.
140:
Thanks to you two! I never had any
interest in necromancy and other
dead people stuff, so you really
helped me out.
144:
That anti-curse or whatever stuff is
suppressing the curse real well!
146:
Only problem is this outfit stands out
a little too much, but I can live with
that.
150:
You're gonna leave out the part
where you were groveling in front of
Adjudicus, huh...
155:
Are you sure it was a good idea to
teach him your techniques?
159:
We didn't really teach him much.
Just gave him the basics. If he
wants to master anything, it's up to
him.
163:
Though I'm truly not sure how that's
going to go...
167:
...Like I said before... What you hear
isn't... the voices of the dead...
172:
Yep, I know. I'm hearing lingering
thoughts and emotions. Not any
active voices.
176:
In other words, it's information in its
purest form! No strings attached!
Talk about a sweet deal!
181: I don't like him. At all.
186: Trust me, you're not the only one.
191:
...Are you sure you're all right with
this? You won't be able to take off
that cryptic artifact for the
foreseeable future.
196:
Of course! Not gonna lie, it was
rough at first, but...
199:
That's just all the more reason to
make sure my suffering was worth
something!
203:
I didn't forge any part of that will! I'm
telling you, all my father's money
belongs to ME!
207:
That's what I call justice! What'd you
think?
210: You've got problems in the head...
223:
Hey, that's pretty mean! All I did was
make sure a dead man's will got
fixed!
226:
You left out the part where you used
this chance to blackmail other
people.
231:
But thanks to that, I got dirt on at
least ten other people! What a deal!
236:
It's a good thing Regitare isn't here.
He would be lamenting the fact that
he helped you...
239:
...Maybe we should rip that artifact
off of you.
244:
Sorry, but I don't intend to part with
my new getup! This thing's way too
useful!
247:
Oh, I hear some more juicy info
coming my way. That's a lot of love
and hate mixed into those lingering
thoughts... I smell drama!
250:
You guys can have front row seats
to it! I hope you're ready!
254: Can I get a refund on my ticket?
259: Don't be like that. We're friends, right?
262:
Watch out, world. The new and
improved Shion is about to change
everything!
